ations--politics, war, diplomacy, and other interstate affairs--as it traces the crucial role played by international organizations in determining the shape of the world today.Iriye's sweeping discussion of international organizations around the world examines multinational corporations, religious organizations, regional communities, transnational private associations, environmental organizations, and other groups to illuminate the evolution and meaning of the global community and global consciousness.While states have been preoccupied with their own national interests such as security and prestige, international organizations have been actively engaged in promoting cultural exchange, offering humanitarian assistance, extending developmental aid, protecting the environment, and championing human rights. In short, they have made important contributions to making the world a more interdependent and peaceful place. This book, tracing the development of the global community in a truly innovative way, will win a wide readership among those interested in understanding the growing phenomenon of globalization and its meaning for us today. Global Community is based on Iriye's Jefferson lectures at the University of California, Berkeley.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aNon-governmental organizations. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh  a19th century.  a20th century.  acontemporary history.  acultural exchange.  adiplomacy.  aengaging.  aenvironmental organizations.  aglobal community.  aglobal politics.  aglobalism.  aglobalization.  ahistorians.  ahistorical.  ahistory buffs.  ainternational drama.  ainternational governments.  ainternational organizations.  ainternational relations.  amodern world.  amultinational corporations.  anational interests.  anonfiction.  apolitical science.  